      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_0_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "sybil_0",
      "description": "Looking for an affordable entry point into vehicle ownership or a solid project car? This no-nonsense vehicle is priced to move and represents genuine value for the budget-conscious buyer. Yes, it shows its age and has seen better days cosmetically, but what you see is what you get \u2014 transparent, straightforward, and honestly priced. Ideal for a mechanically inclined buyer or someone needing basic point-A-to-point-B transportation without breaking the bank. Come take a look and make it yours before it's gone.",
      "price": 5500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there, folks! I've got a real diamond-in-the-rough opportunity for you today! \ud83d\ude97 This trusty ride has seen some adventures and wears its history proudly \u2014 sure, it's got some bumps and bruises along the way, and the interior shows it's been well-loved, but the bones are solid and it's still getting up and going every day! Perfect for a handy buyer looking for a project, a first car that won't break the bank, or someone who just needs reliable transportation without the fancy price tag. A little TLC and this beauty could really shine again! I'm an open book \u2014 come take a look, ask me anything, and let's find the right fit for you. Priced to move and ready for its next chapter!",
      "price": 7500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Here's a solid bones project or daily driver candidate for the mechanically inclined buyer. This unit is riding on a fundamentally sound drivetrain \u2014 the engine turns over with strong compression and the transmission shifts through all gears without slipping or grinding. The suspension geometry is intact with no catastrophic bushing failure, and the brake hardware retains functional stopping capacity front and rear. Yes, the body shows honest road wear \u2014 some surface oxidation, a few stress marks in the sheetmetal \u2014 and the interior has seen better days with wear on the bolster and headliner. But underneath the cosmetic patina, the core mechanicals give you a real foundation to work with. Ideal for a weekend warrior build, a commuter refresh, or a parts-rich acquisition. Priced to reflect its current presentation while rewarding the buyer who knows what to look for under the hood.",
      "price": 7500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    }
